claim.claim-text:
24. A magnetic recording head comprising:
a bottom shield;
a shared pole;
a read element positioned between the bottom shield and the shared pole;
a substantially planar top pole including a rounded top pole body and a pole tip attached to and substantially co-planar with the body, the pole tip having a substantially trapezoidal shape with its major base at the body and its minor base partially defining a medium confronting surface of the pole tip, wherein the top pole is separated from the shared pole by a write gap, and wherein the top pole is in contact with the shared pole; and
a conductive coil positioned such that at least a portion of the conductive coil is positioned between the shared pole and the top pole.
